Note, I really thing we are talking about different markets here
anyway.  If I just wanted to do wordprocessing and balance my
budget on a spreadsheet, than Windows (why NT?) may be the
way to go.  If you are in a different environment, like
academia or the parts of the commercial world where Unix is
used, then Linux would be a much better choice.
   I need to do TCP/IP network programming on a limited budget,
so Linux is for me.


Also be aware that many of your arguments against Linux are
also against Unix in general.  It is not an isolated OS, there
are many, many variants of Unix used everywhere.

